      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ROX THE WORLD (11) has been good from wide barriers in two starts here since a spell. Beaten only 4m fresh then raced three wide without cover but boxed on for second over this distance last week. Peaking now so if he gets the gaps from the back row he could be hard to stop. BEAUDIENE HUNTER NZ (12) was too good as a hot favourite when resuming, racing parked before scoring by 1.6 metres at this circuit and distance. Starts from the back row this time but has upside. DIAMOND WORLD (2) draws nicely and did well for a second from a standing start in a Listed race a week ago. MINOR CATASTROPHE (4) could do better returning to a mobile start.",
